Package Description
de.boereck.matcher
This is the root package for the Case Matcher library.
de.boereck.matcher.eager
This package contains case matching functionality where the object/value to match on is known on definition time of the cases.
de.boereck.matcher.function.curry  
de.boereck.matcher.function.optionalmap
This package contains functional interfaces extending Function mapping to Optional objects.
de.boereck.matcher.function.predicate
This package contains advanced versions of the predicate functional interfaces defined in the JDK package java.util.function.
de.boereck.matcher.function.testable
This package contains a few functional interfaces extending functions from java.util.function, by providing a few more default methods for combining the functions with other functions, especially turning the function into a predicate.
de.boereck.matcher.function.throwing  
de.boereck.matcher.helpers
This package contains a set of classes providing static methods to help defining cases and actions for the Case Match library.
de.boereck.matcher.helpers.found  
This document is the JavaDoc API for the Case Matcher Java library. This library This library provides utility classes that provide functionality to check for cases based on input objects/values and actions that are executed based on this cases. This can be seen as a more enhanced version of Java's switch-case statements. This core library ships with an eager version of matching cases over an input object. To start matching on objects, it is recommended to have a look at the static methods defined in EagerMatcher. When defining match cases, the static functions defined in the helper classes of package de.boereck.matcher.helpers can help to write more concise matching criteria or action code.
